ient to develop insightful understanding of investment target and its industry, including critical industry or market analysis, competitive benchmarking, opportunity assessments, and risk identification through in-depth primary and secondary research- Building detailed financial models for companies under coverage- Creating equity research notes and presentations that include analysis of economic and business cycles, industry value chain, market size, market segments, market shares, market drivers, market trends, products and services- Meeting with the management of companies under coverage, attending quarterly results conference calls, issuing quarterly result update reports, tracking company and sector developments and initiating coverage on uncovered stocks- Performing financial analyses including financial statement analysis and valuation using various techniques including DCF, SOTP, residual value and multiples approach- Discussing results and analysis with buy side clients as well as answering any queries they might have- Coordinating with client sales team on client pitches and relationship maintenanceQualifications-          Experience in equity research or investment banking in China or abroad with a focus on Asia Pacific, having a good understanding of Chinese market is preferred-      Strong analytical and problem solving skills-      Solid report writing and communication skills-      Ability to work effectively under time-sensitive environment-      Be able to take responsibility-      Excellent written and verbal English-      Experienced in PowerPoint, Excel, and Word-      Financial modeling-      Excellent academic track recordLocation: BeijingDuration: PermanentCompensation: Competitive, commensurate with experienceHow to Apply:Please send your CV and cover letter (Chinese and English) to rui_liu@copalamba.net with the subject heading “Recruitment - Equity Research Analyst BJ - Your Name”Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purposes